00:46:06.510 --> 00:46:07.700
Things are very complicated.

00:46:07.700 --> 00:46:08.870
The worlds are different
in different

00:46:08.870 --> 00:46:10.000
countries and all that.

00:46:10.000 --> 00:46:11.880
So people have tried to
do these very simple

00:46:11.880 --> 00:46:12.280
experiments--

00:46:12.280 --> 00:46:14.960
I'll show you-- to try to
convince you that at the most

00:46:14.960 --> 00:46:18.100
fundamental level, very
fundamental levels, depending

00:46:18.100 --> 00:46:21.970
on the culture you come from,
your mind is tuned to see the

00:46:21.970 --> 00:46:25.140
world one way or the other
way relatively speaking.

00:46:25.140 --> 00:46:27.720
And there's variations within
cultures of course.

00:46:27.720 --> 00:46:29.350
But here's a very simple
experiment.

00:46:29.350 --> 00:46:31.910
They show you a box like
this with a line.

00:46:31.910 --> 00:46:34.270
The size of the box and
the line change

00:46:34.270 --> 00:46:36.850
from trial to trial.

00:46:36.850 --> 00:46:38.730
They take it away.

00:46:38.730 --> 00:46:40.070
And now, you see an empty box.

00:46:40.070 --> 00:46:41.530
The empty box could
be the same size,

00:46:41.530 --> 00:46:42.910
or bigger, or smaller.

00:46:42.910 --> 00:46:47.560
And they say, draw a line that
either has the absolute same

00:46:47.560 --> 00:46:50.390
size as this, even though
the box is different.

00:46:50.390 --> 00:46:53.280
Or in other trials, they'll say
draw it so it has the same

00:46:53.280 --> 00:46:56.100
relative, the same ratio,
the same relative size.

00:46:56.100 --> 00:46:57.610
Does that makes sense?

00:46:57.610 --> 00:47:01.260
So here, this would be the same
absolute size, the same

00:47:01.260 --> 00:47:01.990
relative size.

00:47:01.990 --> 00:47:05.300
Here, this would be the same
relative size or absolute.

00:47:05.300 --> 00:47:06.640
Does that makes sense?

00:47:06.640 --> 00:47:09.190
That's all your job
is, draw a line.

00:47:09.190 --> 00:47:12.570
And you're told as it's taken
away, draw the same absolute

00:47:12.570 --> 00:47:15.220
size in the box or the same
relative size, same

00:47:15.220 --> 00:47:17.570
ratio, to the box.

00:47:17.570 --> 00:47:20.480
So here's the first thing to
show you, which is that on

00:47:20.480 --> 00:47:24.740
average people in Japan are
more accurate when they're

00:47:24.740 --> 00:47:27.930
drawing-- this is mean error,
so it's good to be low--

00:47:27.930 --> 00:47:29.770
they're more accurate for
the relative size.

00:47:29.770 --> 00:47:32.340
People in the US, for
the absolute size.

00:47:32.340 --> 00:47:34.990
And I think that's amazing,
a line in a box.

00:47:34.990 --> 00:47:37.610
And we know that's not
culturally taught.

00:47:37.610 --> 00:47:39.170
In United States, we don't have
anybody getting up and

00:47:39.170 --> 00:47:41.040
saying, be all that
you can be!

00:47:41.040 --> 00:47:43.970
Draw that line in
absolute length!

00:47:43.970 --> 00:47:45.850
So the idea is it's not
a taught thing.

00:47:45.850 --> 00:47:46.950
It's a way of thinking.

00:47:46.950 --> 00:47:49.150
And when you get a new example,
you apply your

00:47:49.150 --> 00:47:52.850
culture's way of thinking, many
people much of the time.

00:47:56.470 --> 00:47:58.180
How malleable is that?

00:47:58.180 --> 00:48:00.300
Is that fixed in you
from birth or not?

00:48:00.300 --> 00:48:01.840
And then, you will help
me discover the one

00:48:01.840 --> 00:48:03.190
flaw in this study.

