And a year or two makes the
Japanese look like Americans

00:48:28.360 --> 00:48:28.890
in America.

00:48:28.890 --> 00:48:30.950
Does that make sense?

00:48:30.950 --> 00:48:34.810
So one interpretation is this
is shockingly malleable.

00:48:34.810 --> 00:48:38.920
20 years, 24 years of one
culture, and one or two years

00:48:38.920 --> 00:48:41.800
later, you're shifted into the
mindset of the other culture.

00:48:41.800 --> 00:48:43.460
And maybe that's true.

00:48:43.460 --> 00:48:46.940
If you're a very hard nosed
researcher, what do you wish

00:48:46.940 --> 00:48:47.855
would have happened
in the study to

00:48:47.855 --> 00:48:49.105
convince you that's true?

00:48:52.040 --> 00:48:52.500
Yeah?

00:48:52.500 --> 00:48:53.946
AUDIENCE: Would they
have gone back?

