00:51:36.100 --> 00:51:37.020
Here's another one.

00:51:37.020 --> 00:51:38.270
This was done in the airport.

00:51:38.270 --> 00:51:39.300
Imagine you're in an airport.

00:51:39.300 --> 00:51:42.250
This was in the days before 9/11
so we weren't as worried

00:51:42.250 --> 00:51:44.630
about people running around
airports running up to us.

00:51:44.630 --> 00:51:45.460
Here's how they literally
did it.

00:51:45.460 --> 00:51:47.450
At the San Francisco airport,
they would ask you where

00:51:47.450 --> 00:51:47.960
you're from.

00:51:47.960 --> 00:51:51.290
And if you were from the US or
from Japan or Korea, they

00:51:51.290 --> 00:51:53.530
would open a pencil box
like you might have

00:51:53.530 --> 00:51:54.830
had as a little kid.

00:51:54.830 --> 00:51:56.070
And there'd be a set of
pencils in there.

00:51:56.070 --> 00:51:57.320
And they go, please take one.

00:51:57.320 --> 00:51:59.250
And your first thought is,
OK, what's the deal?

00:51:59.250 --> 00:52:01.020
What's the scam?

00:52:01.020 --> 00:52:02.680
Are there any security
people around?

00:52:02.680 --> 00:52:04.100
They go, no, no, just please
take a pencil.

00:52:04.100 --> 00:52:04.550
And you go, OK.

00:52:04.550 --> 00:52:05.120
And you take one.

00:52:05.120 --> 00:52:06.130
And you think something
bad's going to

00:52:06.130 --> 00:52:06.890
happen, and it doesn't.

00:52:06.890 --> 00:52:08.330
All they want to know is this.

00:52:08.330 --> 00:52:11.330
Do you take the out, the
individualist pencil or the

00:52:11.330 --> 00:52:14.170
collectivist pencil?

00:52:14.170 --> 00:52:16.360
And there's a one in
four condition or a

00:52:16.360 --> 00:52:17.370
two in three condition.

00:52:17.370 --> 00:52:18.730
Which pencil do you take?

00:52:18.730 --> 00:52:22.090
Ridiculous as this experiment
is, it depends

00:52:22.090 --> 00:52:23.450
